\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Now, consider a second limitation to the estimation problem. The visual system does not measure the spectral power distribution directly. Rather, the visual system only encodes the absorption rates of the three different cones. Hence, the nervous system cannot be certain which of the many metameric spectral power distributions is responsible for causing the observed cone absorption rates (see Chapter
\begin_inset space ~

